From: Harninder Rai <harninder.rai@freescale.com>
Date: Mon, 28 Nov 2011 15:50:49 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 81/92] usim: Add device node for USIM in dts

Extracted from 913x_WUSDK_REL_0.9.tar.gz vendor drop.

USIM general and data interrupts are coupled into one IRQ in SoC
Clock prescaler value is fixed to satisfy duty cycle (ISO7816)

Signed-off-by: Ashish Kumar  <ashish.kumar@freescale.com>
Signed-off-by: Harninder Rai <harninder.rai@freescale.com>
Integrated-by: Jiang Bin <bin.jiang@windriver.com>
---
 arch/powerpc/boot/dts/psc9131rdb.dts |   10 ++++++++++
 1 files changed, 10 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)

diff --git a/arch/powerpc/boot/dts/psc9131rdb.dts b/arch/powerpc/boot/dts/psc9131rdb.dts
index f833f9d..5375e8e 100644
--- a/arch/powerpc/boot/dts/psc9131rdb.dts
+++ b/arch/powerpc/boot/dts/psc9131rdb.dts
@@ -340,6 +340,16 @@
 				gpio-controller;
 			};
 
+			sim@11000 {
+				#address-cells = <1>;
+				#size-cells = <1>;
+				compatible = "fsl,sim-v1.0";
+				reg = <0x11000 0x1000>;
+				clock-prescaler = <0xe>;
+				interrupts = <42 2>;
+				interrupt-parent = <&mpic>;
+			};
+
 			L2: l2-cache-controller@20000 {
 				compatible = "fsl,psc9131-l2-cache-controller";
 				reg = <0x20000 0x1000>;
